// SKIP: Mage Armour (an alternative AC calculation of 13 + Dex) is not modeled in the spec — `calculateAC` only supports `Unarmored` (10 + Dex / BarbarianUD / MonkUD) and `WearingArmor`, with no representation of the spell's base AC formula. Additionally, magic item bonuses (+1 to AC) have no field in the `Armor` type, so neither the "can't use Mage Armour while armored" rule nor the "+1 stacks on top of chosen AC calculation" ruling can be encoded against the existing functions.